# <REPLACE: project name>

Workstream-aware research project.

This project starts as a mixed research container. Do not classify the whole
project as Pure Research or R&D. Use `project_state.md` to map the project
intent, current uncertainties, workstreams, dependencies, and project decision
gate.

Workstreams choose the local state object and gate:

- R&D Workstream: `workstreams/<name>/rd_plan.md` and optional
  `workstreams/<name>/prereg/PR_<id>_<slug>.md`
- Phenomenon / Mechanism Research: `workstreams/<name>/prfaq.md` and
  `workstreams/<name>/explanation_ledger.md`

Evidence artifacts under `purposes/` are neutral. Use
`scripts/new_trial.py --project-dir <project> --workstream <name> --slug <slug>`
so the trial cites the selected workstream.

## Boundary contract

**Protocol/state source of truth**: `project_state.md`, `decisions.md`, and the
selected workstream state object.

**Project-instance artifacts**: `configs/`, `src/`, `tests/`, `tracking/`,
`results/`, and `purposes/`.

**Generated report snapshots**: report packages under `results/reports/`,
notebook exports, and trial files are evidence. They do not own research-state
transitions until the selected workstream state object or `decisions.md` cites
them.
